timulate some or make people more aware of the problems.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub147.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm1.showMessage?topicID=36983.topic">PoP encounters that negate melee damage</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub147.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm1.showMessage?topicID=36999.topic">Rant about melee inadequecies, including the raid environment</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
The AE-style attacks of higher end encounters really hurts the ability for melee to move in and attack.  As MT for my guild most of the time this doesn't concern me personally, but I know that all our melee spend time trying to joust around the AE's or using ranged attacks to do damage.  With the persistance of AE rampage going off frequently though, this renders jousting into a risk since they can easily be killed in one rampage round.  Unless you can sustain high DPS in these kinds of fights with ranged attacks, then you're useless.  I know warriors and rogues have higher archery caps to do some decent damage but still this pales in comparison to their melee, and for other melee aside from rangers ranged attacks aren't viable.<br>
<br>
The only solution I can think offhand is to do something like reduce the range of AE rampage to just shy of the max melee range to allow people to melee, or reduce the frequency or damage of the rampage.  Increase any AE's to compensate.  This way, melee can do their thing without fear of dying in one round of rampage.  I still want these fights hard, but the current state of AE Rampage is stupid unless you intend to send waves of melee in to get cut down instantly by it.<br>
<br>
Thoughts, comments, ideas?<br>
<br>
-- Parv, LoS <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tremainbladesinger>TremainBladesinger</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/15/03 10:18 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.theunholytrinity.org/cracks_smileys/cwm/big/firemad.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Decline of melee in PoP</span><hr size=1> If the problem is the developers wanting an encounter with a really high damage output and not make melee completely useless just make the AE/rampage range extremely long so casters get hit too, that way everyone is screwed equally and the fight isnt gimped. <p>&quot;the day i die will be the day i shut my mouth and put down my sword&quot; - Tremain, 65 Overlord<br>
