<br>
There have always been fights where it was preferential to have melee stand off, from Kunark to Pop, but the isssue now is the sheer number of fights where it's just far more practical to not have melee really even participate.<br>
<br>
AE rampage needs to be redone first of all.  The ideal solution is instead of removing it, to simply make the rampage hits for LESS than their main target hits.  I'd say (AE) rampage hits for around 10-20% of their max but tunable per fight.<br>
<br>
So something could hit the MT for 2k, but would only AE rampage for in the 200s, which even when quaded is something that would be manageable.<br>
<br>
As far as AOEs go, they need to alter a lot of them.  They changed the resist system around before pop, and yet because of what they did, it's still all but useless and doesn't matter.<br>
<br>
They need to alter the AOEs to not all be, all or nothing.  The damage you take should scale with your resists because even at 500 in a resist, you can just not resist an aoe or two and you're dead.  A 3k AOE wouldn't be terribly bad IF, you could partially resist damage because of your resist levels.  <br>
<br>
The saddest part is, that as they jack the numbers up, AE rampaging for 1k+, huge AOEs, the difficulty generally goes down since less people generally participate and it comes down to one single thing, keeping the MT alive.  A 3k AOE landing on a MT that's being healed by 10+ healers is just a tiny blip on the radar and means nothing.  AE rampage means jack when no one else is even around. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=darkhosis>Darkhosis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/17/03 7:07 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.cox-internet.com/hosis/dingo.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Decline of melee in PoP</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>AE rampage needs to be redone first of all. The ideal solution is instead of removing it, to simply make the rampage hits for LESS than their main target hits. I'd say (AE) rampage hits for around 10-20% of their max but tunable per fight.<br>
