<br>
If AE rampage did such a miniscule amount of damage, it'd be trivial.  If it does too much, it unfairly penalizes melees.   If you're in a cleric shortage situation, most melees have to just sit back and use ranged weapons.  But AE rampage fights pale in comparison to some of the AEs, like Blazzax has an AE that's so damaging that the cleric will likely run out of mana or die from having to cast WoR a couple times a minute if you're in a melee group that has to charge to do tangible damage.  Some people would suggest having an AE &quot;caller&quot; but it simply isn't feasible.. you can't hide behind walls anymore.  For a 30 second recast AE you'd spend a good 50% of your time running back and forth and waiting for AE calls, that's 50% less damage.. and instead of being outdamaged 1.5 or 2x by ranged combatants, you're being outdamaged 3 or 4x.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>AE rampage means jack when no one else is even around. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
